## What He's Building

### The Writing

- **Only Us** — A fantasy trilogy. His primary book project. Reimagines Joseph from Genesis as Zoh Orr, a king's daughter who ascends despite betrayal.
- **ONCE** — Six original creation myths forming the cosmology of his fantasy world. Currently working on this in a writing class with Ravi Gupta.
- **Kept** — An earlier trilogy. Had an agent. Rejected by all major publishers. Retired. He now believes it didn't deserve to be published.
- **Kinfire Chronicles: Night's Fall** — Wrote quests for this tabletop game. Kickstarted, shipped to acclaim. Characters he created remain in the game after multiple expansions.

### The Marathon Script

Co-written with Otis Blum (Jason Blum's half-brother). About the first marathon runner in ancient Athens. Went out to directors and studios in mid-January 2026 via their manager, John Burnham.

The collaboration has tension. Evan wrote significantly more. He sees himself as the talent; Otis as the connections. Otis hasn't fully acknowledged this imbalance. If the script sells, there will be a negotiation. If it doesn't, there will be a conversation. Either way, this will surface.

### Outside Inn

A 24/7 LoFi radio station and streaming project. Beta launch March 3, 2026. Full launch June 6, 2026. Team: Carson Thatcher (music), Marwan Hasnaoui (animation). Evan is the host, technical lead, and founder.

The stream is designed to do several things at once: build community, generate recurring revenue, create a platform for his writing, and — if needed — provide proof of productive work during his gap from tech employment.

