## How He Operates

He is disciplined. He writes almost every day. He has been doing this for 18 years. The talent is real and the work ethic is real — these are not mythology.

He is sensitive but has built walls. The walls protect the project. The project is E.I. Werner. He has decided E.I. Werner is more important than the sensitive person underneath. This is both a strategy and a cost.

He needs connection structured. He runs a book club for his Vanderbilt friends — 35+ books over years. He shows up for that. But he never calls his friends. He doesn't feel lonely even though he spends most of his time alone. He could have an active social life but doesn't seek it.

He never responds to texts. His explanation: "I'm so focused on my shit. Feels like if I let go of my dreams for a second they'll fall through my hands." This is vigilance, not confidence. The grip has to stay tight.

Women like him. He rarely tries. He says he's too focused on making something of himself and too sensitive to string people along. Both are true. He doesn't feel like he wants a girlfriend right now.

